<item>
 <title>WRI: Priority Fields for International Collaboration</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/library/wri-priority-fields-international-collaboration</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/an_emerging_revolution-5.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;109&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-library-file&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Library File:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;div class=&quot;filefield-file&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf&quot;  alt=&quot;application/pdf icon&quot; src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/wri_priority_fields_for_international_collaboration.pdf&quot; type=&quot;application/pdf; length=640492&quot;&gt;wri_priority_fields_for_international_collaboration.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Author:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    World Resources Institute        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In November 2007, the MOST and National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC) jointly launched the International Science and Technology Cooperation Program on New and Renewable Energy. The program’s goals are twofold: diversifying the sources of technology imports, and expediting technology transfer processes between China and other countries. The program has identified five priority technologies for international collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/library/wri-priority-fields-international-collaboration&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
